When diagnosing performance, leverage observability:

### Metrics-Driven Diagnosis
- Before profiling, check existing metrics: are counters, histograms, and gauges already exposing the bottleneck?
- If metrics are missing for the hot path, add them as part of the optimization — future regressions need detection.
- Compare metrics before and after optimization to prove improvement quantitatively.

### Trace-Driven Analysis
- Use distributed tracing spans to identify which component contributes most to latency.
- Look for span gaps — time not accounted for by child spans indicates hidden overhead.
- Check for excessive logging in hot paths — structured logging has a cost at high throughput.

### Observability of Optimizations
- Every optimization should be measurable via existing or new metrics.
- Add benchmark results to the diagnosis document alongside metric deltas.
- Set up alerting thresholds based on the new performance baseline.
